         <entry xml:id="anperin-dlgenr"
                xml:lang="en"
                type="mainEntry"
                prev="#anfaqinon-dlgenr"
                next="#onqos-dlgenr"
                source="Genesis Rabbah">
            <form type="lemma" opt="false">
               <orth type="lemma" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false" select="true">אנפרין</orth>
               <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾnpryn</orth>
               <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">ʾanperin</pron>
               <gramGrp opt="false">
                  <gram type="pos" opt="false">noun</gram>
                  <gram type="gen" opt="false">m.</gram>
                  <gram type="num" opt="false">pl.</gram>
               </gramGrp>
               <form type="variant" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">אמפרין</orth>
                  <orth type="transliteration" xml:lang="fjb" opt="false">ʾmpryn</orth>
                  <pron notation="rabbinic" opt="false">ʾamperin</pron>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="61,5 - Vat1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">לומפרין</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="61,5 - K V" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">לופרין</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="61,5 - Ox1" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">לפרין</orth>
               </form>
               <form type="variant" source="61,5 - Ox2" opt="false">
                  <orth type="variant" xml:lang="jpa" opt="false">לפדין</orth>
               </form>
            </form>
            <sense xml:id="anperin-dlgenr-1" opt="false">
               <usg type="domain" opt="false">occupations</usg>
               <usg type="socioCultural" norm="borrowing" opt="false">core borrowing</usg>
               <usg type="normativity" opt="false">standard</usg>
               <usg type="meaningType" opt="false">lit.</usg>
               <usg type="frequency" opt="false"/>
               <usg type="geographic" opt="false"/>
               <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en" subtype="sense">
                  <quote>traders</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="translationEquivalent" xml:lang="grc">
                  <usg opt="false">
                     <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
                  </usg>
                  <quote>ἔμποροι</quote>
               </cit>
               <cit type="example" xml:lang="jpa">
                  <quote>
                     ויוקשן ילד את שבא ואת דדן ובני דדן היו אשורים ולטושים ולאומים. ר' שמואל בר נחמן אמר אפעלגב דאינון מתרגמין ואמרין תגרין ואנפרין וראשי אומין כולהם ראשי אומות הם.
         </quote>
                  <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                     <ref type="witness">61,5</ref>
                     <ref type="witness">II 663: 6</ref>
                  </bibl>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">לומפרין</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">לופרין</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">לפרין</ref>
                  <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">לפדין</ref>
                  <cit type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                     <quote>“And Jokshan begot Sheba, and Dedan. And the sons of Dedan were Asshurim, and Letushim and Leumim” (Gen 25,3). R. Shemuʾel bar Naḥman said: Although they [the meturgamanin in the Synagogues] translate and say: “merchants” [for Asshurim], “traders” [for Letushim] and “heads of peoples” [for Leumim], yet they were all heads of peoples. (cf. Freedman / Simon II 565)</quote>
                  </cit>
                  <note anchored="true">=
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq 109 (32c: 551)</bibl> (<term xml:lang="jpa">ולופרין</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Yalq Chr. 1 1073 (516c: 52-53)</bibl> (in the name of R. Shimʿon b. Gamliʾel) (<term xml:lang="jpa">ולופרין</term>);
            <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">SekhT (Buber) Ḥayye Sarah 25,3</bibl>
                  </note>
               </cit>
            </sense>
            <etym type="borrowing" opt="false">
               <lbl opt="false">source language</lbl>
               <lang opt="false">Ancient Greek+</lang>
               <cit type="etymon" xml:lang="grc">
                  <xr type="related" opt="false">
                     <lbl opt="false">Cf. LSJ</lbl>
                     <ref target="https://www.perseus.tufts.edu/hopper/text?doc=Perseus%3Atext%3A1999.04.0057%3Aalphabetic+letter%3D*e%3Aentry+group%3D93%3Aentry%3De%29%2Fmporos"
                          type="entry">ἔμπορος, ΙΙΙ.</ref>
                  </xr>
               </cit>
            </etym>
            <note anchored="true">Reading of <bibl type="ancient" default="false" status="draft">Targ. Jonathan on Gen 25,3</bibl>. Cf. MY ad loc.;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Levy I 99</bibl>;
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">Jastrow I 78</bibl>.
      <bibl type="modern" default="false" status="draft">AC I 124</bibl> suggests also „Verständiger, Scharfsinniger“ (“intelligent, ingenious”) for Gr. <term xml:lang="grc">ἔμφρων</term>. However, this is the reading of BM and Vat 2 only, while all other mss and parallels read
      <ref type="entry" xml:lang="jpa">לופרין</ref>.
   </note>
            <ref type="bibliography">
               <bibl default="false" status="draft">
                  <title>Krauss, LW II</title>
                  <citedRange>61</citedRange>
               </bibl>
            </ref>
         </entry>
